# Git commit author

When creating git commits in this repository, **never** use `cursoragent@cursor.com` or other Cursor default agent emails.

Use this identity via environment variables (do **not** run `git config`):

- **Name:** `fcursor`
- **Email:** `fcursor@iwantmoneyfromcursor.com`

Example:

```bash
export GIT_AUTHOR_NAME="fcursor"
export GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL="fcursor@iwantmoneyfromcursor.com"
export GIT_COMMITTER_NAME="fcursor"
export GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL="fcursor@iwantmoneyfromcursor.com"
git commit -m "your message"
```

Or inline for a single commit:

```bash
GIT_AUTHOR_NAME="fcursor" GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL="fcursor@iwantmoneyfromcursor.com" \
GIT_COMMITTER_NAME="fcursor" GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL="fcursor@iwantmoneyfromcursor.com" \
git commit -m "your message"
```
